  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the University of Western Ontario (UWO) does not have a formal policy that grants a specific percentage boost, such as 4%, to high school students applying from Alberta. Admissions criteria can vary by program, and decisions are typically based on a holistic review of the applicant's academic performance, extracurricular activities, and other factors.\n\nHowever, policies may change, and different programs may have their own specific requirements or considerations. I recommend checking UWO's official admissions website or contacting their admissions office directly for the most current and accurate information regarding admissions policies and any potential adjustments for students from specific provinces.",
